Response Text: Number one, I'm extremely underimpressed by your choices of art in public places. We need to be taking risks, making moves. We couldn't be any further off the map in the art world. We are nonexistent. Next time y'all make a board of people to decide how to spend your money: include artists! I can hardly believe some of the things I've seen money spent on --- those blue flappers on Lamar come to mind and that dumb troll. Austin is an outdoor city. We need outdoor art, outdoor events, but SMALL. Like, as in, they don't actually ruin the park they're in. THAT's the Austin I miss. Small, amazing thing popping up in your local park, on a random corner in your neighborhood.... Not F1. Not ACL. Not stuff that's so big that I wouldn't go to it even if I didn't hate what it does to our city. Big, loud, no thank you.

